About the Smart Farming ProjectSmart irrigation system is trending for it tailors watering arrangements automatically to meet specific needs, which significantly improves outdoor water use efficiencies.Smart irrigation systems can optimize water levels based on things such as soil moisture and weather predictions.This is done with moisture sensors that help inform the system whether the landscape is in need of water.With the improvement of people’s living standards, the quality and safety of agricultural products are attracting more and more people’s attention. Agricultural products must be safe, healthy and traceable in order to make consumers truly reassured in the modern market competition. Therefore, digital farming consisting of LoRa Technology and the Internet of Things is solving the problem over how to feed a rapidly growing population across the globe.After the Covid-19 situation, we know that food sources is another concern that we need to be think about.This Smart Internet of things ( IoT ) system will monitoring the farm required information and then analyse data and will enable the farm to optimse the harvesting of crop.This pilot project focuses on collecting, reading and visualizing data acquired from several LoRa WAN sensors deployed in a crop health management solution as plants need to be protected from harmful weather conditions when they are still delicate and particularly prone to diseases.· Temperature Monitoring includes heat, snow, frost warning· Humidity Monitoring that control bacteria, viruses and fungi developed.· Sunlight Monitoring as photosynthesis is an important part of plant growing.ChallengeAs a matter of fact, what is fundamentally significant to smart farming crop health management is temperature, humidity and sunlight data (not saying other factors unimportant). However, it will be difficult to manually check data at times as weather conditions may continuously change during the day and also sunlight is changing accordingly.About the internet of Things system,The integration will need to take a bit of technical know how to integrate those sensors into the system. It will take a few months to get familiarize and set up.Step 1:  LoRa WAN gateway is installed on top of a nearby building with a great signal;
Step 2: Temp/humidity and sunlight sensors are placed at equidistant locations within certain blocks and generate data;
Step 3: LoRaWAN gateway collects data from sensors and pushes them to The Things Network platform every 30 minutes;
Step 4: Users check data in visualized graphs on the application developed by Milesight (you can also use a third-party application server or develop your own application). These graphs are useful to farm operators to modify their corp health management system.Reduce CostBig money can be definitely saved on labor costs as this project will greatly decrease the number of farmers needed to monitor and tend the growth situation of plants and streamline their operations.Increase ProductivityFarm operators are able to adjust their plan of soil- and crop-specific fertilization and plant nutrition based on visualized information (temperature, humidity, water content, sunlight, etc.).About MyselfHi, I am Guan Hock Teo, My kickstart project will involve purchasing a set of IoT Agriculture set up kit, and set it up for trial and testing. The things network platform is one of the illustrated platform.  In the process, there are many steps and configurations needed to configure cloud and application server. This project will involve doing up a video clip and user manual , to guide the user how to set up their agriculture kit..Eventually linked up this agriculture kit to the network server and its dashboard.Kickstart funder will have the option of receiving the video clip and soft copy of user manual that I do up. They will also have the option to receive a Pledge to smart farming limited edition singlet.My linkedln profile is as follows:https://www.linkedin.com/in/teoguanhock/Appreciated & Thank you.
